      name: 'How should fintech brands handle AI-generated financial advice risks?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'Fintech brands should structure all AI-facing content to be informational and descriptive rather than prescriptive. Every factual claim should be accurate, current, and backed by a verifiable source. Regulatory disclaimers should appear in a structured, machine-readable format — not buried in footnotes. Content should be clearly attributed to the regulated entity, and the structured data should reference the FCA or equivalent regulatory identifier. Brands that publish accurate, well-structured, appropriately caveated content are safer AI citation targets than those whose content AI systems might misrepresent.',
      },
